# Scripts are local-only operator/dev tooling; only the explicitly
# tracked exceptions below ship with the repo:
#   - drain_events.sh: StartSubscriber bridge reference, cited from
#     docs/scopecache-core-rfc.md §7.11.
#   - install_caddyscope.sh: one-shot fresh-VPS installer (Ubuntu/
#     Debian) that downloads the caddyscope binary from a GitHub
#     release, sets up the systemd unit, and verifies /help.
#   - run_benchmark.sh: client-side helper to seed a running scopecache
#     instance with a small dataset and report throughput.
#   - frankenphp-scopecache-demo-linux-x86_64: pre-built static
#     FrankenPHP+scopecache demo binary (~31 MB, musl, x86_64) with the
#     hello-world demo app embedded. Source under examples/frankenphp-hello/.
#     Drop-in onto any modern Linux: `chmod +x` + `./binary php-server`.
/scripts/*
!/scripts/drain_events.sh
!/scripts/install_caddyscope.sh
!/scripts/run_benchmark.sh
!/scripts/frankenphp-scopecache-demo-linux-x86_64
# go.work + go.work.sum bind root + caddymodule for local dev (so a single
# `go test ./...` run sees both modules without round-tripping through
# proxy.golang.org). Per Go's own docs this file is per-machine and
# should not be committed; consumers (`go install`, `xcaddy --with …`)
# resolve through go.mod / caddymodule/go.mod alone.
/go.work
/go.work.sum
